I"L<p>Facebook has dominated the news headlines of late, but not for good reasons. There were the <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/mar/22/cambridge-analytica-scandal-the-biggest-revelations-so-far">50 million Facebook profiles gathered for Cambridge Analytica</a> and used in the 2016 presidential election. <a href="https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2018/03/facebook-scraped-call-text-message-data-for-years-from-android-phones/">Facebook has long been scraping call and text message data</a> from Android phones. And within the Facebook iOS app, the company pushes the Onavo Protect VPN, an app made by a subsidiary that <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2018/02/12/facebook-starts-pushing-its-data-tracking-onavo-vpn-within-its-main-mobile-app/">literally collects all your mobile data traffic for Facebook</a>.</p>
